Find products never ordered.
Tables: orders, products

SELECT p.product_id, p.product_name
FROM products p 
LEFT JOIN orders o ON p.product_id = o.product_id
WHERE o.product_id IS NULL;

I used LEFT JOIN to retrieve all records from products table and matching records from orders table.
If no matching values in orders table, then columns are returned as NULL.
Then, filtering WHERE o.product_id IS NULL for the products never ordered as the records of those products never existed in orders table.
